  "title": "DH Solution Consulting Engineer (FT Handler)",
  "description": "<p>The CoE Engineer for handler (SOC HPC) acts as the technical consultant for handling and thermal for FT-Handler solutions. This role bridges R&D, field service, and global application teams to ensure robust, efficient, and scalable (Technologies Integration) of handling solutions. Focuses on driving innovation, supporting customer engagements, and enabling global knowledge transfer.</p><p><u><strong>Job Duties and Responsibilities:</strong></u><br /><br /><strong>1. Product & Process Expertise</strong></p><ul><li>Define effective NPI-solution setups for handling and thermal management with new technologies integration solutions.</li><li>Validate mechanical, thermal and automation performance under real-world conditions.</li></ul><p><strong>2. Innovation & Influence</strong></p><ul><li>Collaborate with R&D to influence design for better reliability and performance (throughput, stability).</li><li>Drive improvements in FT-handling, thermal management and automation relevance with customers’ needs and market demands.</li></ul><p><strong>3. Customer & Field Support</strong></p><ul><li>Participate in strategic customer engagements, especially for new handling solution introductions.</li><li>Provide consulting and troubleshooting for NPI & solution-integration support, related to mechanical (probe) alignment, thermal control, and automation efficiency.</li></ul><p><strong>4. Knowledge Transfer</strong></p><ul><li>Facilitate technical transfer to field engineers and customers.</li><li>Conduct workshops and online sessions on handler operation and optimization know-how to support teams globally.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Required Job Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Bachelor’s Degree in Mechatronics /Electronics/Thermal Engineering</li><li>Deep understanding of semiconductor package handling and thermal technologies.</li><li>Global mindset and industrial knowledge to influence design decisions on technical, operational and business needs. </li><li>Strong troubleshooting and problem-solving skills.</li><li>Excellent communication for customer consulting, technical sharing and R&D collaboration.</li></ul><p><strong>Required Job Experience: </strong></p><ul><li>5+ years in semiconductor equipment (FT-handler), thermal and related automation systems.</li><li>Hands-on experience with mechanical alignment, thermal control, and device handling.</li><li>Flexible and available for short-notice business travel, extended working hours, and weekend/holiday support to ensure critical project delivery or escalation management.</li></ul>",
